# Agent Review

Load and follow `~/.agents/skills/agent-review/SKILL.md`.

Claude bridge:

- Use `Task` for isolated reviewer/auditor work; follow `runtime-harnesses.md` only for capability caveats.
- For other-authored or unknown-author PRs, run `pr-necessity-auditor` first and block reviewer fan-out until it greenlights that the PR is worth reviewing further.
- After any required PR necessity greenlight, launch two concurrency-safe `reviewer` tasks in parallel with distinct review angles. Use model overrides `opus` and `sonnet` when available.
- After reviewers finish, apply the controller parity filter from `agent-review/SKILL.md`; select the concrete live-UI target packet and run `live-ui-review` when changed paths or kept candidate findings touch UI/runtime behavior and runtime evidence is applicable, then carry any screenshot handoff into final output.
- Run the findings audit after live UI returns or is explicitly skipped; delegate to `findings-auditor` only for non-trivial candidate sets or fix diffs, otherwise audit inline.
- Treat reviewer-reported `verification_needed` as controller-owned: run needed heavy/mutating/shared-resource checks serially only after aggregation, or surface them as blockers/uncertainty.
- Keep all worker/auditor/live tasks investigation-only; this controller owns judgment and gated side effects.
